title: mirek92
author: mirek92
content: Hello, I minted new token in bsc scan one hour ago. I saw succesfull status but now I still see:Â  This transaction has been included and will be reflected in a short while.When will be token contract visible in bsc scan?Thank you for reply.

comments.author: saxydev
comments.body: Usually it happens after 1-2 minutes, it will help if you will post the txd or the contract address here.

comments.author: Bitcoin_Arena
comments.body: You have got to practice some patience. The message is very clear on this: "This transaction has been included and will be reflected in a short while."What's the hurry for?

comments.author: vv181
comments.body: The information text you received indicates that the transaction is already been propagated/sent within the network but it is still pending/unconfirmed. The hint that it will get reflected in a while doesn't quite accurate. It depends on the current network congestion and the GAS fee that you've paid, so it could be the reason why it has been an hour ago, but at that time it doesn't get confirmed yet.You can see the rough estimation of the current mempool on https://bscscan.com/gastracker, but since you are created a new token, surely it requires a much higher amount than a simple transaction/transfer.
